alternative_parents.description: Aliphatic Hydrocarbons that contains one or more unsaturated carbon atoms. These compounds contain one or more double or triple bonds.
alternative_parents.name: Unsaturated aliphatic hydrocarbons

class.description: Hydrocarbons that contains one or more unsaturated carbon atoms. These compounds contain one or more double, triple, or aromatic bonds.
class.name: Unsaturated hydrocarbons

description: This compound belongs to the class of organic compounds known as terminal alkynes. These are alkynes featuring a carbon substituent on one acetylenic carbon, and a hydrogen on the other carbon.

direct_parent.description: Alkynes featuring a carbon substituent on one acetylenic carbon, and a hydrogen on the other carbon.
direct_parent.name: Terminal alkynes

intermediate_nodes.description: Acyclic hydrocarbons containing one or more acetylene groups.
intermediate_nodes.name: Acyclic acetylenes

intermediate_nodes.description: cyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbons having a carbon-carbon triple bond and the general formula CnH2n-2.
intermediate_nodes.name: Alkynes

kingdom.description: Compounds that contain at least one carbon atom, excluding isocyanide/cyanide and their non-hydrocarbyl derivatives, thiophosgene, carbon diselenide, carbon monosulfide, carbon disulfide, carbon subsulfide, carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, Carbon suboxide, and dicarbon monoxide.
kingdom.name: Organic compounds

subclass.description: Acyclic (branched or unbranched) and cyclic (with or without side chain) hydrocarbons having one or more carbon to carbon triple bonds.
subclass.name: Acetylenes

superclass.description: Organic compounds made up only of carbon and hydrogen atoms.
superclass.name: Hydrocarbons
